# audiospread

Minimal CLI tool to spread audio output across multiple sinks
using PipeWire / PulseAudio.

## Features

- Multi-output audio (no sink limit)
- Toggle on/off
- Dynamic sink detection
- PipeWire compatible
- Window-manager friendly
- No volume handling (by design)

## Requirements

- PipeWire or PulseAudio
- pactl

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/youruser/audiospread.git
cd audiospread
chmod +x audiospread
ln -s $(pwd)/audiospread ~/.local/bin/audiospread

## Usage

```bash
audiospread toggle
audiospread on
audiospread off
audiospread status

##Roadmap
v1.1: volume sync & mute
v2.0: profiles & persistence

